      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like this function isn\u0027t used yet, but for these AssertionResult helpers I recommend manually managing the result instead of using EXPECT_*.  In this case, it will output an error to the console but then ImageMatches will return success, so anything that does EXPECT_TRUE(ImageMatches(...)) will say it succeeds.\n\nIn this case, I would either early-out with the result or keep track of failures.\n\nOption 1:\ntesting::AssertionResult result \u003d RowMatches(...);\nif (!result) {\n    return result;\n}\n\nOption 2:\nint rowMismatches \u003d 0;\nfor (...) {\n    testing::AssertionResult result \u003d RowMatches(...);\n    if (!result) {\n        ++rowMismatches;\n    }\n}\n\nif (rowMismatches) {\n    return testing::AssertionFailure() \u003c\u003c rowMismatches \u003c\u003c \" rows mismatch.\";\n} else {\n    return testing::AssertionSuccess();\n}",
